The paper deals with algorithms for testing equivalence of polynomials, which is a problem in computational complexity. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of randomness and black-box access to circuits, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper mentions the Polynomial Identity Testing (PIT) problem, which is a well-studied problem in algebraic complexity theory, indicating that it could also be classified under cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
